Subject: [PATCH 5/9] bridge phase 4: port sessionRunner.ts (child-CLI spawner)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Ports typescript/src/bridge/sessionRunner.ts → src/bridge/session_runner.py.
Provides the child-CLI spawner used by Phase 6 (replBridge) and Phase 8
(bridgeMain) to launch local Claude Code processes and parse their NDJSON
stdout for activity events + control_requests + first user message.

Phase 5 remote_bridge_core does NOT use this module — it's an in-process
v2 bridge with no local subprocess.

Surface:
- create_session_spawner(deps) -> SessionSpawner — factory
- build_child_env(parent, opts) — allowlist-based env builder; strips
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN, DB passwords, etc.
- safe_filename_id(value) — path-traversal-safe ID
- extract_activities(line, sid, on_debug) — NDJSON activity parser
- BuildChildEnvOpts, SessionSpawnerDeps, PermissionRequest types
- CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST, TOOL_VERBS constants
- MAX_ACTIVITIES, MAX_STDERR_LINES = 10
- Internal _SpawnedSession implements SessionHandle with: session_id,
  access_token, activities, current_activity, last_stderr (properties),
  wait_done (async), kill, force_kill, write_stdin, update_access_token

Key behaviors:
- asyncio.create_subprocess_exec with piped stdin/stdout/stderr
- Ring buffers via collections.deque(maxlen=N)
- Allowlist-based env construction; secrets in parent never inherited
- update_access_token sends NDJSON line via stdin so child refreshes
  without restart
- SIGTERM → 'interrupted', exit 0 → 'completed', other → 'failed'
- Transcript file (jsonl) opened alongside debug log when configured

CRITIC review (2 rounds, APPROVE):
- BLOCKING fix: timestamp in milliseconds (matches TS Date.now()) not
  seconds; pinned with regression test.
- BLOCKING fix: transcript file handle leak on async cancellation;
  outer try/finally + open AFTER successful spawn.
- MAJOR fix: get_event_loop() in __init__ raises on Python 3.12+;
  done_future created lazily on first start()/wait_done().
- MAJOR fix: kill()/force_kill() raced with subprocess creation;
  latched via _kill_requested flag so requests issued before
  _process is set are honored once it becomes ready. Pinned with
  test_kill_before_spawn_ready_still_terminates_child.
- Polish: write_stdin exception catch broadened to OSError+RuntimeError;
  outer try/finally now resolves done_future as 'failed' on unexpected
  unwind so wait_done() awaiters don't hang during shutdown.

43 new tests, 494/494 bridge tests pass overall.

